# Git Commit Rules

## Author Line

All commit messages MUST include an author line at the end of the body:

```text
Author: cabynum <cbynum@gmail.com>
```

## Commit Message Format

```text
<short summary line>

- Bullet point describing change 1
- Bullet point describing change 2
- ...

Next: <what comes next, if applicable>

Author: cabynum <cbynum@gmail.com>
```

## Example

```text
Add meal suggestion feature

- Implement random pairing algorithm
- Add "Try Another" button
- Handle edge case when no sides exist

Next: Add meal plan persistence

Author: cabynum <cbynum@gmail.com>
```

## Repository Identity

This project uses personal credentials (not work):

- **Name**: cabynum
- **Email**: cbynum@gmail.com

This is configured locally in `.git/config` for this repo only.
